notesStmt.note: This meeting happens in the course of a day in which a task force works on issues related to establishing collaborations among European universities and developing joint degrees. The members of the task force have previously split into two working groups, with one group focusing on administrative and one group focusing on academic aspects regarding the development of joint degrees. In this meeting, the two groups come together again and discuss their suggestions and questions they have collected. S1 is the chair of the meeting and also the speaker of the academic group. She starts by summarizing the questions put forward by the academic group. She has handwritten notes to help her summarize all the questions. She generally formulates her sentences freely, but towards the end of her summary she partly reads from her notes, which is indicated in the transcript. After S1's summary, S4 summarizes the outcomes of the brainstorming done by the administrative group and the other speakers add comments. A discussion about the different project phases emerges, then S4 resumes his summary. The meeting ends with a short discussion on how the task force and the project should proceed.
